while True:
  s1 = list(input())
  if s1 == ["-"]:
    break
  s2 = list(input())
  s1.reverse()
  s2.reverse()
  under = list(input())
  under.reverse()
  right = []
  center = s2.pop()
  while s1 or s2:
    if under and center == under[-1]:
      center = s1.pop()
      under.pop()
    else:
      right.append(center)
      center = s2.pop()
  if not under:
    right.append(center)
  print("".join(right))

while(1):
    up=raw_input()
    if up=='-':    break
    left=raw_input()
    down=raw_input()
    
    cen=left[0]
    idu=0
    idd=0
    idl=0
    ans=''
    for i in range(len(up)+len(left)-1):
        if down[idd]==cen: #moved down
            cen=up[idu]
            idu+=1
            idd=min(idd+1,len(down)-1)
        else:
            ans+=cen
            idl+=1
            cen=left[idl]
    ans+=cen
    print ans

# AOJ 1036: Monster Factory
# Python3 2018.7.6 bal4u

while True:
	in1 = list(input())
	if in1[0] == '-': break
	in2 = list(input())
	out = list(input())
	k = in2.pop(0)
	ans, f = '', True
	while len(in1) or len(in2):
		if len(out) and out[0] == k:
			k = in1.pop(0)
			del out[0]
		else:
			ans += k
			if len(in2): k = in2.pop(0)
			else:
				f = False
				break
	if f: ans += k
	print(ans)
